{
  "texts": [
    "That is to say the seller can dynamically adjust the sales strategy for individual customers by immediately providing the customer with a selection of relevant options upon website arrival.",
    "Doing so, the customer benefits from being offered an assortment of suitable options and the seller profits from increased sales due to personalized assortments.",
    "• Modelling challenges: The sheer mass and dimensionality of data available in online settings come with modelling challenges as demand models are not necessarily able to deal with large amounts of data, i.e.",
    "with a high number of observations, or high-dimensional data, i.e.",
    "data containing lots of different information for each customer."
  ]
}